# Git operations (agents)

**Before any commit, push, tag, or release-related action:** read and follow `.github/instructions/git/git-policy.instructions.md`.

## Commits (checklist)

- Subject: conventional `type(scope): subject` (allowed types in `commitlint.config.mjs`)
- Body: terse `-` bullet points only — not prose paragraphs
- Multiline messages: `git commit -F <message-file>` (not inline `-m` heredocs)
- Optional `Verification:` section with short bullets
- **Never** `Co-Authored-By`
- Only commit when the user explicitly asks

## Push / remote

- Do not `git push` unless the user explicitly asks in the current message
- Do not create remote branches or worktrees unless asked

## Releases

Human-only — see git-policy for the full deny list. Clarify ambiguous requests (e.g. "ship it") before acting.
